en if only {\textasciitilde}20\% of this power could be captured, it could satisfy 100\% of the world’s energy demand for all purposes (6995–10177 Mtoe) and over seven times the world’s electricity needs (1.6–1.8 TW). Several practical barriers need to be overcome to fully realize this potential.},
